# CSS layout (responsive)

This project uses Tailwind CSS and DaisyUI. Layouts must adapt to viewport and container size. Use **flex** and **grid** with fluid sizing. Do not pin page structure to fixed pixel widths or heights.

Sources: [Tailwind responsive design](https://tailwindcss.com/docs/responsive-design), [MDN min-width](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Reference/Properties/min-width), CSS Flexbox spec (automatic minimum size).

## Core rules

1. **Grid for page structure, flex for components inside.** Grid handles 2D layout (rows + columns). Flex handles 1D layout (a row or a column).
2. **Avoid fixed layout sizes.** No `w-[480px]`, `h-[32rem]`, or inline `width`/`height` for structure.
3. **Prefer fluid sizing:** `w-full`, `max-w-*`, `flex-1`, `grow`, `shrink`, `fr`, `minmax(0, 1fr)`.
4. **Mobile first.** Unprefixed classes = all screens (including mobile). `md:` means "768px and up", not "on mobile". Never use `sm:` alone to target phones.
5. **Use `gap` for spacing** in flex/grid. Avoid margin hacks between siblings.
6. Match patterns in `Layout.tsx` and `PageHeader` before inventing new systems.
7. **Height chain stuck?** Try flex + `min-h-0` first. If still broken, use CSS variables with `calc()` (not fixed px/`rem` heights).

## Flex vs grid

| Use case | Tool | Tailwind example |
|----------|------|------------------|
| Nav, toolbar, title + action | flex | `flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4` |
| Page shell, sidebar + main | flex | outer `flex flex-col`; main `flex-1 min-w-0` |
| Card grids, dashboards, forms | grid | `grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4` |
| Auto-wrapping tiles (no breakpoints) | grid | `grid-cols-[repeat(auto-fit,minmax(min(100%,16rem),1fr))]` |

Combine both: grid for the page, flex inside each section/card.

## Critical: `min-w-0` / `min-h-0`

Flex items default to `min-width: auto`, so they refuse to shrink below content width. This breaks truncation, scroll regions, and nested flex layouts.

Add `min-w-0` (or `min-h-0` on column flex) on any flex child that should shrink, scroll, or truncate. Chain it up the flex hierarchy if overflow persists.

If height still will not chain correctly (nested cards, fixed headers/footers, virtual lists), do not fall back to raw pixel heights. Use **CSS variables + `calc()`** so the scroll region stays viewport-relative.

```tsx
// Parent defines measurable regions once
<div
  className="flex flex-col min-h-0"
  style={
    {
      '--step-header': '5.5rem',
      '--step-actions': '4rem',
    } as React.CSSProperties
  }
>
  <header className="shrink-0">…</header>
  <div className="min-h-0 overflow-y-auto h-[calc(100dvh-var(--step-header)-var(--step-actions)-2rem)]">
    …
  </div>
  <footer className="shrink-0">…</footer>
</div>
```

Rules for CSS var + calc fallbacks:

- Define vars on the nearest layout ancestor (`--header-h`, `--footer-h`, `--toolbar-h`).
- Prefer `100dvh` / `100svh` over `100vh` on mobile.
- Subtract padding and gaps in `calc()`, not as magic numbers in `height: 500`.
- Keep vars in `rem` when tied to UI chrome; use `calc()` to compose the final size.
- Try flex + `min-h-0` first; use vars + calc only when the height chain is still broken.

```tsx
<div className="flex min-w-0">
  <div className="flex-1 min-w-0 truncate">…</div>
</div>
```

## Container queries (reusable components)

When the same component appears in a sidebar, main column, and modal, viewport breakpoints are wrong. Use container queries so the component responds to its parent width.

```tsx
<div className="@container">
  <div className="flex flex-col @md:flex-row gap-4">…</div>
</div>
```

Use viewport breakpoints for global layout (nav, page shell). Use `@container` for components reused in multiple regions.

## Fixed sizes (sparingly)

| OK | Avoid for layout |
|----|------------------|
| `max-w-7xl mx-auto w-full` (readability cap) | `w-[480px]`, `h-[32rem]` |
| Icon/avatar sizes (`size-4`) | `height: 500` inline styles |
| Small input widths (`w-28` on a filter) | Arbitrary `p-[37px]`, `gap-[13px]` |
| Virtual-list scroll parent height | Fixed column widths on tables |
| CSS vars + `calc()` for bounded scroll areas | Raw `height: 500`, `h-[32rem]` when flex chain fails |

Prefer Tailwind scale tokens (`p-4`, `gap-4`, `text-sm`) over bracket values.

For fluid type, prefer `text-sm md:text-base` or `clamp()` over fixed `text-[18px]`.

## Common patterns

```tsx
// Page shell
<div className="min-h-screen flex flex-col">
  <main className="flex-1 min-w-0 w-full max-w-7xl mx-auto p-4 lg:p-8" />
</div>

// Responsive grid
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 xl:grid-cols-3 gap-4">…</div>

// Intrinsic grid (wraps without breakpoints)
<div className="grid grid-cols-[repeat(auto-fit,minmax(min(100%,16rem),1fr))] gap-4">…</div>

// Scroll region in a flex card
<div className="card-body flex flex-col min-h-0">
  <div className="flex-1 min-h-0 overflow-y-auto">…</div>
</div>

// Tables on small screens
<div className="overflow-x-auto">…</div>
```

## Before finishing

- [ ] Structure uses flex or grid, not stacked divs with fixed dimensions
- [ ] Flex children that scroll/truncate have `min-w-0` / `min-h-0`
- [ ] Mobile layout uses unprefixed classes; larger screens add `sm:`/`md:`/`lg:`
- [ ] Checked at 320px, 375px, 768px, and 1024px
- [ ] Reusable components in varying contexts use `@container`, not only viewport breakpoints
- [ ] If flex height chain fails, used CSS variables + `calc()` instead of fixed pixel heights
